(grunting)

33
00:02:19.535 --> 00:02:21.303
(phone rings)

34
00:02:24.641 --> 00:02:26.041
Are you going to answer that?

35
00:02:26.075 --> 00:02:27.109
No.

36
00:02:27.143 --> 00:02:29.011
DORIAN:
It's Samantha.

37
00:02:29.045 --> 00:02:31.179
Yep.

38
00:02:31.214 --> 00:02:32.481
Hey. no. Dorian...

39
00:02:32.515 --> 00:02:33.715
Uh. John Kennex's line.

40
00:02:33.750 --> 00:02:35.284
Uh. he does not

41
00:02:35.318 --> 00:02:36.985
wish to speak
with you right now.

42
00:02:37.020 --> 00:02:38.687
He is waving his hands.

43
00:02:38.721 --> 00:02:39.988
gesturing "no."

44
00:02:42.292 --> 00:02:43.492
Yes. I understand.

45
00:02:43.526 --> 00:02:45.794
I hate it
when he does that. too.

46
00:02:46.729 --> 00:02:47.969
Yeah. I know.

47
00:02:47.997 --> 00:02:49.531
That's the least
of his problems.

48
00:02:49.565 --> 00:02:50.832
Okay.

49
00:02:50.867 --> 00:02:52.167
You take care.

50
00:02:52.201 --> 00:02:54.002
Would you like me
to relay her message?

51
00:02:54.037 --> 00:02:55.938
No. I think I got it.

52
00:02:55.972 --> 00:02:57.406
Thanks.

53
00:02:57.440 --> 00:03:00.676
Do you want to talk about it?

54
00:03:00.710 --> 00:03:03.111
Samantha and I
had dinner last night...

55
00:03:03.146 --> 00:03:04.866
and the hologram
of her roommate and her mom

56
00:03:04.881 --> 00:03:06.682
and her therapist.
Every single call

57
00:03:06.716 --> 00:03:07.716
she got. she took.

58
00:03:07.750 --> 00:03:08.917
She holo-blocked you.

59
00:03:08.952 --> 00:03:11.320
Exactly. I mean.
whatever happened

60
00:03:11.354 --> 00:03:13.789
to two people just sharing
a meal and connecting. you know?

61
00:03:13.823 --> 00:03:15.524
- I know.
- You wouldn't know.

62
00:03:15.558 --> 00:03:17.960
Why am I asking you?
You wouldn't have a clue.

63
00:03:17.994 --> 00:03:20.596
Well... and I'm
just positing this...

64
00:03:20.630 --> 00:03:21.830
perhaps you're boring.

65
00:03:21.864 --> 00:03:24.233
Boring?
You're calling me boring?

66
00:03:24.267 --> 00:03:25.901
We need to talk about guy code.

67
00:03:25.935 --> 00:03:27.102
There's certain things
you don't do...

68
00:03:27.136 --> 00:03:28.537
Hey. I need you to help me

69
00:03:28.571 --> 00:03:29.638
check out a possible homicide.

70
00:03:29.672 --> 00:03:30.952
Sure. When did the call come in?

71
00:03:30.974 --> 00:03:32.407
It didn't.

72
00:03:32.442 --> 00:03:34.109
There's no sign of forced entry.
no struggle.

73
00:03:34.143 --> 00:03:36.311
No foul play indicated at all.

74
00:03:36.346 --> 00:03:38.447
EMTs are calling it
cardiac arrest.

75
00:03:38.481 --> 00:03:39.815
I don't understand.

76
00:03:39.849 --> 00:03:41.149
Why is it considered
a possible homicide?

77
00:03:41.184 --> 00:03:42.417
The victim's a chrome.

78
00:03:42.452 --> 00:03:44.119
We're genetically engineered.

79
00:03:44.153 --> 00:03:45.621
We don't die young.

80
00:03:56.466 --> 00:04:00.068
The deceased's name
is Brian Barrow. 28.

81
00:04:00.103 --> 00:04:03.071
Bond trader
at Kane Asset Management.

82
00:04:03.106 --> 00:04:05.607
JOHN: Explains the view.
Anything missing?

83
00:04:05.642 --> 00:04:07.943
According to the report. no.

84
00:04:07.977 --> 00:04:10.812
Rules out robbery as a likely motive.
Medical history?

85
00:04:10.847 --> 00:04:12.147
Typical chrome.

86
00:04:12.181 --> 00:04:13.248
No health issues.

87
00:04:13.283 --> 00:04:16.318
World-class athlete.
a swimmer.

88
00:04:16.352 --> 00:04:18.854
He competed in the
Detroit Olympics of 2036.

89
00:04:18.888 --> 00:04:20.923
There's no logical explanation
for this.

90
00:04:20.957 --> 00:04:22.491
How could he die like this?

91
00:04:22.525 --> 00:04:23.926
We should do a toxicology.

92
00:04:23.960 --> 00:04:27.062
Maybe EMTs got it right:
heart attack.

93
00:04:27.096 --> 00:04:30.232
No. When a chrome is designed.
every box is checked:

94
00:04:30.266 --> 00:04:32.467
health. beauty. intelligence.

95
00:04:32.502 --> 00:04:34.403
Look. I know chromes
aren't supposed to have

96
00:04:34.437 --> 00:04:37.105
congenital defects;
perfect genes and all that.

97
00:04:37.140 --> 00:04:38.907
Chromes don't normally
become cops. either.

98
00:04:38.942 --> 00:04:41.009
There's a first time
for everything.

99
00:04:41.044 --> 00:04:43.011
DORIAN:
Look at this.

100
00:04:44.658 --> 00:04:46.658
There's a half-millimeter
puncture wound

101
00:04:46.683 --> 00:04:48.050
at the base of his skull.

102
00:04:48.084 --> 00:04:49.885
It goes all the way
to his cerebral cortex.

103
00:04:49.919 --> 00:04:52.399
JOHN:
Can you get any DNA?

104
00:05:07.403 --> 00:05:08.470
Something wrong?

105
00:05:08.504 --> 00:05:10.105
If this is the entry point

106
00:05:10.139 --> 00:05:12.641
to something that killed him.
the DNA indicates

107
00:05:12.675 --> 00:05:15.544
that Brian Barrow was murdered
by seven different people.

108
00:05:17.914 --> 00:05:21.850
JOHN: Alec Govain.
Philip Moses makes seven.

109
00:05:21.885 --> 00:05:23.085
And these are the seven people

110
00:05:23.086 --> 00:05:24.486
whose DNA we found in the wound?

111
00:05:24.520 --> 00:05:25.687
Of the murder victim?

112
00:05:27.023 --> 00:05:29.391
DORIAN: Whatever weapon was used
to kill Brian Barrow

113
00:05:29.425 --> 00:05:31.326
was contaminated by the DNA
of all these people.

114
00:05:31.361 --> 00:05:32.427
MALDONADO:
Did you locate them?

115
00:05:32.462 --> 00:05:34.142
JOHN:
They're all dead.

116
00:05:35.647 --> 00:05:37.008
DORIAN:
They're all listed as dying

117
00:05:37.033 --> 00:05:39.167
of natural causes.
Their hearts stopped.

118
00:05:40.470 --> 00:05:42.404
What do you think's
going on. John?

119
00:05:42.438 --> 00:05:46.008
I don't know. but I doubt
they died of natural causes.

120
00:05:46.042 --> 00:05:47.843
MALDONADO:
Are these people chromes?

121
00:05:47.877 --> 00:05:50.646
They are not. but they must
have been chosen for a reason.

122
00:05:50.680 --> 00:05:52.481
Do you think we stumbled
upon a serial killer?

123
00:05:52.515 --> 00:05:54.549
JOHN: Yeah. If he hadn't
killed the chrome.

124
00:05:54.584 --> 00:05:55.945
we never would have
picked this up.

125
00:05:55.952 --> 00:05:57.419
It would be pretty easy to miss

126
00:05:57.453 --> 00:05:59.054
a little pinprick
on the back of the neck.

127
00:05:59.088 --> 00:06:00.422
What do they have in common?

128
00:06:00.456 --> 00:06:01.657
They all lived in city limits.

129
00:06:01.691 --> 00:06:03.425
Other than that. our algorithms

130
00:06:03.459 --> 00:06:04.726
didn't pick up any patterns.

131
00:06:04.761 --> 00:06:06.261
I see one pattern.

132
00:06:06.296 --> 00:06:09.331
They're all very attractive.

133
00:06:18.875 --> 00:06:21.076
(computer trills. beeping)

134
00:06:29.419 --> 00:06:31.887
(knocking)

135
00:06:50.573 --> 00:06:52.107
Do it again.

136
00:06:58.748 --> 00:07:00.916
We have to stop.

137
00:07:00.950 --> 00:07:05.487
You will do what I want.
or I will call

138
00:07:05.522 --> 00:07:07.222
the police.
and you will go to jail

139
00:07:07.257 --> 00:07:08.557
for the rest of your life

140
00:07:08.591 --> 00:07:11.159
for practicing
with a revoked license.

141
00:07:11.194 --> 00:07:13.295
Your choice.

142
00:07:39.022 --> 00:07:41.823
(machinery whirs)

143
00:07:41.858 --> 00:07:43.992
(gasps)

144
00:07:51.067 --> 00:07:53.702
(screams)

145
00:08:01.551 --> 00:08:03.185
Someone's been talking
to the press

146
00:08:03.220 --> 00:08:04.987
about the chrome murder.

147
00:08:05.022 --> 00:08:06.422
You're kidding. Already?

148
00:08:06.456 --> 00:08:07.923
"Metro Police hunt for
possible serial killer

149
00:08:07.958 --> 00:08:09.225
targeting the city's
young and beautiful."

150
00:08:09.259 --> 00:08:11.894
<i>L.A. Times. New York Times.</i>
<i>AP Deathwire.</i>

151
00:08:11.928 --> 00:08:13.496
My comm's been
ringing off the hook.

152
00:08:13.530 --> 00:08:14.830
We don't even know
anything yet.

153
00:08:14.865 --> 00:08:16.365
and they're already
talking about it.

154
00:08:16.400 --> 00:08:18.434
VALERIE: This kind of news sells.
Chromes have ears

155
00:08:18.468 --> 00:08:20.403
all over the city.
and they take care of their own.

156
00:08:20.437 --> 00:08:22.004
Now. I have a lead.

157
00:08:22.039 --> 00:08:23.873
Two hours before
the victim was killed.

158
00:08:23.907 --> 00:08:26.075
he was at the Electus Club
on Remington.

159
00:08:26.109 --> 00:08:27.677
Killer could have followed him
from the club.

160
00:08:27.711 --> 00:08:29.478
I'll check it out.

161
00:08:29.513 --> 00:08:31.180
Actually. I should go.

162
00:08:31.214 --> 00:08:32.848
Alone.

163
00:08:33.817 --> 00:08:35.184
The Electus is a chrome club.

164
00:08:36.119 --> 00:08:37.987
Of course. Makes sense.

165
00:08:38.021 --> 00:08:39.889
We'll go check in with Rudy.

166
00:08:39.923 --> 00:08:43.092
The bodies of the other victims
are on the way to him.

167
00:08:43.126 --> 00:08:45.287
If they have the same wounds
on the back of their neck.

168
00:08:45.295 --> 00:08:46.896
maybe he can find out
what killed them.

169
00:08:48.396 --> 00:08:50.876
You sure you're up for
going to the chrome club?

170
00:08:50.901 --> 00:08:53.102
Yeah. They may not respect
what I've done with my life.

171
00:08:53.136 --> 00:08:55.504
but they sure respect
what I can do for theirs.

172
00:08:55.539 --> 00:08:57.673
You were the first one they
called when Brian Barrow died.

173
00:08:57.708 --> 00:09:00.188
Only because they're
praying it was murder.

174
00:09:00.210 --> 00:09:01.977
If Brian Barrow died
of natural causes.

175
00:09:02.012 --> 00:09:03.379
the chromes would have
to face something

176
00:09:03.413 --> 00:09:04.747
they never thought possible.

177
00:09:04.781 --> 00:09:07.950
The whole selling point of being
a chrome is a long life.

178
00:09:07.985 --> 00:09:09.318
And perfect health.

179
00:09:09.353 --> 00:09:12.321
People pay a lot of money
for perfection.

180
00:09:12.356 --> 00:09:15.024
Let me know
if you need anything.

181
00:09:23.667 --> 00:09:25.568
Robert. Violet. welcome.

182
00:09:25.602 --> 00:09:27.570
Nice to see you.

183
00:09:29.339 --> 00:09:30.673
I'm sorry.

184
00:09:30.707 --> 00:09:32.074
This is a private club.

185
00:09:33.407 --> 00:09:35.287
I'm sorry. too.
that I'm a member.

186
00:09:35.312 --> 00:09:37.246
Detective Valerie Stahl.

187
00:09:37.280 --> 00:09:39.548
I need to see your surveillance
data from yesterday.

188
00:09:39.583 --> 00:09:41.217
You're a police officer?

189
00:09:41.251 --> 00:09:42.491
You're a chrome.

190
00:09:42.519 --> 00:09:43.986
Yeah. I just
showed you my badge.

191
00:09:44.021 --> 00:09:45.901
and I know you have
20/20 vision.

192
00:09:45.922 --> 00:09:48.224
20/10. And I'm afraid
I can't help you.

193
00:09:48.258 --> 00:09:49.759
I'm investigating the murder

194
00:09:49.793 --> 00:09:51.193
of a chrome named Brian Barrow.

195
00:09:51.228 --> 00:09:53.429
I'm sure you heard about it
on the news.

196
00:09:53.463 --> 00:09:55.064
As general manager.
I'm responsible for protecting

197
00:09:55.098 --> 00:09:56.565
the privacy of our members.

198
00:09:56.600 --> 00:09:58.267
Maybe I'm not making
myself clear.

199
00:09:58.301 --> 00:10:00.469
We believe his killer may have
followed him from here.

200
00:10:00.504 --> 00:10:03.305
In that case. he would show up
on the police drones.

201
00:10:03.340 --> 00:10:04.580
wouldn't he?

202
00:10:04.608 --> 00:10:06.275
Again. this is a private...

203
00:10:06.310 --> 00:10:08.744
Club. Yes. I know. and I'm sure
you're smart enough to know

204
00:10:08.779 --> 00:10:10.146
that I can get a search warrant

205
00:10:10.180 --> 00:10:11.480
in about 45 seconds.

206
00:10:11.515 --> 00:10:12.915
And you must be
smart enough to know

207
00:10:12.916 --> 00:10:14.150
that I can get
Chief Judge Thorne

208
00:10:14.184 --> 00:10:15.718
to quash it
ten seconds after that.

209
00:10:15.752 --> 00:10:17.887
- He's a member.
- I guess I'll just be forced

210
00:10:17.921 --> 00:10:19.422
to cut your police patrol
by 50%.

211
00:10:19.456 --> 00:10:21.457
- Is that supposed to scare me?
- Should.

212
00:10:21.491 --> 00:10:23.192
Based on statistical models.
it'll trigger

213
00:10:23.226 --> 00:10:25.461
a 32% rise in violent attacks
in the area.

214
00:10:25.495 --> 00:10:27.163
Criminals find out we're not
patrolling like we used to.

215
00:10:27.197 --> 00:10:29.131
and they're gonna
take advantage.

216
00:10:29.166 --> 00:10:31.367
Before you know it.
this is a high-incident area.

217
00:10:31.401 --> 00:10:33.035
You know how that works.

218
00:10:33.070 --> 00:10:34.337
We don't need the police.

219
00:10:34.371 --> 00:10:35.492
We have private security.

220
00:10:35.505 --> 00:10:36.939
You mean the guy in the hallway

221
00:10:36.974 --> 00:10:38.975
violating the concealed
weapons statute 49B?

222
00:10:39.009 --> 00:10:42.311
That's a lot to sweep under
the rug. even for Judge Thorne.

223
00:10:42.346 --> 00:10:44.680
- Sorry. Is there a problem?
- Yeah.

224
00:10:44.715 --> 00:10:46.215
Do you have anyone
a little more formidable?

225
00:10:46.249 --> 00:10:47.350
(quiet laugh)

226
00:10:47.384 --> 00:10:48.985
Oh. not me.

227
00:10:49.019 --> 00:10:50.252
I bruise easily.

228
00:10:50.287 --> 00:10:51.687
Chromes don't bruise easily.

229
00:10:51.722 --> 00:10:53.055
Ah. you are

230
00:10:53.090 --> 00:10:55.124
a good police officer.
I'm the owner.

231
00:10:56.326 --> 00:10:57.426
You want to sit?

232
00:10:57.461 --> 00:10:58.861
I'd love to.

233
00:10:58.895 --> 00:11:01.063
Jake Bellman.

234
00:11:06.854 --> 00:11:08.814
DORIAN:
<i>Do you think it was a chrome</i>

235
00:11:08.839 --> 00:11:10.172
that leaked our investigation
to the press?

236
00:11:10.207 --> 00:11:11.447
It's possible.

237
00:11:11.475 --> 00:11:13.142
They got a lot of
pull in this town.

238
00:11:13.176 --> 00:11:14.543
Do you know
how many murders there are

239
00:11:14.578 --> 00:11:15.845
in this city every year?

240
00:11:15.879 --> 00:11:17.813
- 756.
- Yeah. a lot.

241
00:11:17.848 --> 00:11:19.808
One of them turns out to
be a chrome. and suddenly

242
00:11:19.816 --> 00:11:21.884
the whole world stops.

243
00:11:21.918 --> 00:11:23.486
Just proves my point.

244
00:11:23.520 --> 00:11:24.654
What point?

245
00:11:24.688 --> 00:11:26.389
That technology. in this case

246
00:11:26.423 --> 00:11:27.790
chromes.

247
00:11:27.824 --> 00:11:29.225
is driving a wedge
between people.

248
00:11:29.259 --> 00:11:31.360
Making it us versus them.

249
00:11:31.395 --> 00:11:34.196
Technology. like being
holo-blocked on a date.

250
00:11:34.231 --> 00:11:36.098
I thought we agreed
that you had a bad date

251
00:11:36.133 --> 00:11:37.333
because you're boring.

252
00:11:37.367 --> 00:11:39.969
You just can't handle the fact

253
00:11:40.003 --> 00:11:42.204
that technology's
part of the problem.

254
00:11:42.239 --> 00:11:43.773
Cuts a little close
to the titanium.

255
00:11:43.807 --> 00:11:47.043
No. in fact. I'm excited
to embrace this new.

256
00:11:47.077 --> 00:11:49.278
- anti-tech lifestyle.
- Really?

257
00:11:49.313 --> 00:11:50.913
On the way back
to the precinct.

258
00:11:50.948 --> 00:11:53.416
let's replace your robotic leg
with a tree limb.

259
00:11:53.450 --> 00:11:55.751
Or maybe something useful.
like a shovel.

260
00:11:55.786 --> 00:11:57.253
I wish I had a shovel.

261
00:11:59.400 --> 00:12:01.400
JAKE BELLMAN:
<i>I was an attorney at 18.</i>

262
00:12:01.425 --> 00:12:03.192
so I know that detectives

263
00:12:03.226 --> 00:12:05.061
can't cut police patrols.

264
00:12:05.095 --> 00:12:06.362
(quiet laugh)

265
00:12:06.396 --> 00:12:08.297
I'm gonna get that footage

266
00:12:08.332 --> 00:12:10.099
one way or the other.

267
00:12:11.268 --> 00:12:12.802
A chrome was killed.

268
00:12:12.836 --> 00:12:14.270
A member of your club.

269
00:12:14.304 --> 00:12:15.805
One of your own.

270
00:12:15.839 --> 00:12:17.873
We want to know
what the story is.

271
00:12:17.908 --> 00:12:21.077
Okay. well. I want to know
what your story is.

272
00:12:21.111 --> 00:12:23.913
Why. 'cause I'm
a police officer?

273
00:12:23.947 --> 00:12:25.448
I'm a curiosity to you?

274
00:12:25.482 --> 00:12:28.451
No. but I am curious.

275
00:12:29.486 --> 00:12:31.420
It's a long story.

276
00:12:31.455 --> 00:12:32.622
Well. I've got time.

277
00:12:32.656 --> 00:12:35.458
Yeah? You don't need
to get back to your club?

278
00:12:35.492 --> 00:12:37.727
No.

279
00:12:37.761 --> 00:12:40.129
Being a cop. it's
not the strangest

280
00:12:40.163 --> 00:12:41.998
life choice I've
heard for a chrome.

281
00:12:42.032 --> 00:12:44.133
You know.
my brother's a sculptor.

282
00:12:44.167 --> 00:12:47.069
You want to know
what his medium is?

283
00:12:47.104 --> 00:12:48.671
Sure.

284
00:12:48.705 --> 00:12:49.839
You ever heard of a chain saw?

285
00:12:49.873 --> 00:12:51.807
Yes.
Chain saw and lumber.

286
00:12:51.842 --> 00:12:53.476
That's his medium.

287
00:12:53.510 --> 00:12:55.678
Not too many galleries
for something like that.

288
00:12:55.712 --> 00:12:57.813
I think they kind of

289
00:12:57.848 --> 00:13:00.249
overdid his creative gene.

290
00:13:00.284 --> 00:13:02.685
I can imagine you'd know
how my parents felt

291
00:13:02.719 --> 00:13:05.354
having a chrome who didn't
meet their expectations.

292
00:13:07.691 --> 00:13:09.125
You pity him?

293
00:13:09.159 --> 00:13:11.427
(laughs)
No. He pities us.

294
00:13:11.461 --> 00:13:13.429
He's proud to call himself
a sculptor.

295
00:13:13.463 --> 00:13:14.864
He's happy.

296
00:13:14.898 --> 00:13:16.732
What about you?

297
00:13:16.767 --> 00:13:18.301
You proud to call yourself
a police officer?

298
00:13:18.335 --> 00:13:19.869
Yes.

299
00:13:19.903 --> 00:13:23.673
Even in front of other chromes?

300
00:13:23.707 --> 00:13:25.007
(sighs)

301
00:13:25.042 --> 00:13:27.343
I told you it's a long story.

302
00:13:27.377 --> 00:13:29.278
Are you happy?

303
00:13:31.214 --> 00:13:32.682
Yeah. I am.

304
00:13:32.716 --> 00:13:35.351
Every time I get a bad guy.

305
00:13:38.689 --> 00:13:40.957
Then let's get you
that surveillance video.

306
00:13:41.595 --> 00:13:43.635
FEMALE REPORTER:
<i>Updating our top story...</i>

307
00:13:43.660 --> 00:13:46.095
police officials
refuse to confirm

308
00:13:46.129 --> 00:13:49.098
an investigation into
the so-called beauty killer.

309
00:13:49.132 --> 00:13:51.033
But sources close to the probe

310
00:13:51.068 --> 00:13:53.736
say the hunt
for a possible serial murderer

311
00:13:53.770 --> 00:13:56.005
is underway and intensifying.

312
00:13:56.039 --> 00:13:58.274
This is Claire Chang re...

313
00:13:58.308 --> 00:14:00.309
- Rudy.
- Oh! (groans)

314
00:14:00.344 --> 00:14:01.377
You're here.

315
00:14:01.411 --> 00:14:04.013
Finally. (sighs)

316
00:14:04.047 --> 00:14:06.349
Mausoleum dropped off three
of the exhumed bodies

317
00:14:06.383 --> 00:14:07.717
an hour ago.

318
00:14:07.751 --> 00:14:08.784
And...

319
00:14:08.819 --> 00:14:10.353
you were right.

320
00:14:10.387 --> 00:14:12.888
Vir-topsy reveals
that all seven of them

321
00:14:12.923 --> 00:14:16.025
have the same wound. uh.
at the base of the neck.

322
00:14:16.059 --> 00:14:17.460
They were indeed murdered.

323
00:14:17.494 --> 00:14:19.262
Have a look.

324
00:14:20.573 --> 00:14:22.374
JOHN:
Any idea what caused it?

325
00:14:22.399 --> 00:14:23.933
I might. yeah.

326
00:14:26.303 --> 00:14:28.237
Something wrong?

327
00:14:29.573 --> 00:14:32.041
You've got this "beauty killer"
out there.

328
00:14:32.075 --> 00:14:34.043
and I have to hear
about it on the news.

329
00:14:34.077 --> 00:14:35.544
You don't think to warn me?

330
00:14:36.813 --> 00:14:37.780
What's the difference

331
00:14:37.814 --> 00:14:40.583
between me and all seven
of these victims?

332
00:14:40.617 --> 00:14:42.418
Hmm? I'll tell you.

333
00:14:42.452 --> 00:14:44.120
They're all dead.

334
00:14:44.154 --> 00:14:46.088
You're worried
that you're gonna be targeted?

335
00:14:46.123 --> 00:14:48.090
I was a child model.

336
00:14:48.125 --> 00:14:49.559
I-I have
a Rothschild's nose.

337
00:14:49.593 --> 00:14:51.894
My grandmother's
a sixth cousin of the heir.

338
00:14:51.929 --> 00:14:53.729
(laughing)

339
00:14:54.998 --> 00:14:56.399
(clears throat)

340
00:15:00.571 --> 00:15:02.038
It was an oversight. Rudy.

341
00:15:02.072 --> 00:15:03.105
Uh. we're sorry.

342
00:15:03.140 --> 00:15:04.273
Duly noted.

343
00:15:04.308 --> 00:15:05.575
So what did you find?

344
00:15:05.609 --> 00:15:06.943
Something in the wound.

345
00:15:06.977 --> 00:15:09.912
First centimeter.
a very clean insertion point.

346
00:15:09.947 --> 00:15:11.380
consistent with a needle.

347
00:15:11.415 --> 00:15:13.816
After that. it gets weird.
It's irregular.

348
00:15:15.786 --> 00:15:17.853
JOHN:
Looks like tiny

349
00:15:17.888 --> 00:15:19.789
claw marks.
They are.

350
00:15:19.823 --> 00:15:21.090
From nanobots.

351
00:15:21.124 --> 00:15:22.158
Nanobots?

352
00:15:22.192 --> 00:15:23.726
Are you saying

353
00:15:23.760 --> 00:15:25.595
robots were injected
into their necks.

354
00:15:25.629 --> 00:15:28.431
crawled inside their skulls
and killed them?

355
00:15:28.465 --> 00:15:30.266
Yeah. same as Brian Barrow.

356
00:15:30.300 --> 00:15:31.701
In fact. they found

357
00:15:31.735 --> 00:15:33.469
two of these things
still inside him.

358
00:15:33.503 --> 00:15:35.571
I call them Mike and Ike.

359
00:15:35.606 --> 00:15:39.408
Any idea what Mike and Ike
are designed to do?

360
00:15:39.443 --> 00:15:40.676
I'm working on it.

361
00:15:46.116 --> 00:15:48.017
Great work at the Electus Club.

362
00:15:48.051 --> 00:15:50.653
I'm amazed they gave up
the tape without a fight.

363
00:15:50.687 --> 00:15:53.522
Thanks.

364
00:15:53.557 --> 00:15:55.424
What's on your mind?

365
00:15:55.459 --> 00:15:57.026
I'm thinking
maybe it wasn't so bad

366
00:15:57.060 --> 00:15:59.462
being around chromes after all.

367
00:15:59.496 --> 00:16:00.997
The last time
you dealt with chromes.

368
00:16:01.031 --> 00:16:03.165
you were at the shooting range
for three hours.

369
00:16:03.200 --> 00:16:05.001
Poor targets didn't know
what hit them.

370
00:16:05.035 --> 00:16:07.036
Yeah. well...

371
00:16:07.070 --> 00:16:10.339
I guess we can all be surprised.

372
00:16:10.374 --> 00:16:13.109
I spent so much time resenting
where I came from

373
00:16:13.143 --> 00:16:15.344
that I forgot
they're people. too.

374
00:16:16.847 --> 00:16:18.147
You know. sometimes it's nice

375
00:16:18.181 --> 00:16:20.249
to connect with people
who are like you.

376
00:16:20.284 --> 00:16:21.617
who understand you.

377
00:16:21.652 --> 00:16:23.986
Is that why you keep
Kennex around?

378
00:16:24.021 --> 00:16:25.121
No.

379
00:16:25.155 --> 00:16:26.322
I lost a bet.

380
00:16:26.356 --> 00:16:27.890
(laughs)

381
00:16:27.925 --> 00:16:30.192
MAN:
Captain.

382
00:16:31.295 --> 00:16:33.775
Looks like facial rec
has a match.

383
00:16:35.365 --> 00:16:37.266
(cell phone rings)

384
00:16:37.301 --> 00:16:38.501
Stahl.

385
00:16:38.535 --> 00:16:40.436
Hey. I got the footage
from the Electus Club.

386
00:16:40.470 --> 00:16:41.737
I'm sending you a file.

387
00:16:41.772 --> 00:16:42.939
What do you got?

388
00:16:42.973 --> 00:16:45.608
I have Brian Barrow
leaving the club at 5:30.

389
00:16:45.642 --> 00:16:47.009
Keep watching... There!

390
00:16:47.044 --> 00:16:48.277
You see that?

391
00:16:48.312 --> 00:16:49.512
The guy in the coat?

392
00:16:49.546 --> 00:16:51.681
Yup. I think that's our guy.

393
00:16:51.715 --> 00:16:53.516
He follows Barrow
down Remington.

394
00:16:53.550 --> 00:16:54.984
Comes around Sixth Avenue.

395
00:16:55.018 --> 00:16:56.786
And then I get
a facial recognition

396
00:16:56.820 --> 00:16:58.754
from the Bitcoin exchange
across the street.

397
00:16:58.789 --> 00:17:01.357
Comes up as Alec Govain.

398
00:17:01.391 --> 00:17:02.358
That's one of the dead victims.

399
00:17:02.392 --> 00:17:03.392
Correct.

400
00:17:03.427 --> 00:17:04.961
It's not over.

401
00:17:04.995 --> 00:17:06.362
He comes around the next corner.

402
00:17:06.396 --> 00:17:08.731
Now a camera from the cab stand
picks him up.

403
00:17:08.765 --> 00:17:11.000
This time. facial rec reads him
as Todd Paxton.

404
00:17:11.034 --> 00:17:12.368
JOHN:
Another victim.

405
00:17:12.402 --> 00:17:15.404
How could one man
come up on facial rec

406
00:17:15.439 --> 00:17:16.806
as two different people?

407
00:17:16.840 --> 00:17:18.674
I think I have an answer.

408
00:17:24.648 --> 00:17:26.849
There you are.
Thank you.

409
00:17:31.822 --> 00:17:33.623
Can... can I help you?

410
00:17:33.657 --> 00:17:35.791
One large nitro.

411
00:17:35.826 --> 00:17:37.360
Coming right up.

412
00:17:37.394 --> 00:17:39.161
RUDY:
<i>What these nanobots</i>

413
00:17:39.196 --> 00:17:41.998
are programmed to do.
they read and reconstruct

414
00:17:42.032 --> 00:17:43.533
facial tissue.

415
00:17:43.567 --> 00:17:45.001
What did he say?

416
00:17:45.035 --> 00:17:46.769
He said our killer is stealing

417
00:17:46.803 --> 00:17:48.471
<i>parts of people's faces.</i>

418
00:17:48.505 --> 00:17:53.075
Did anyone ever tell you
you have very pretty eyes?

419
00:17:53.110 --> 00:17:56.946
RUDY: <i>This is about
nanobot plastic surgery.</i>

420
00:18:07.064 --> 00:18:09.365
Dr. Randolph Amir.

421
00:18:09.399 --> 00:18:12.134
Excuse me. Excuse me!

422
00:18:12.169 --> 00:18:14.103
(door opens) Stop! You're
not allowed to be in...

423
00:18:14.137 --> 00:18:15.638
Dr. Randolph Amir?

424
00:18:15.672 --> 00:18:17.640
- Yes. - We understand
that you're involved

425
00:18:17.674 --> 00:18:18.974
in the research

426
00:18:19.009 --> 00:18:21.143
into nanobot
facial reconstruction.

427
00:18:21.178 --> 00:18:23.879
Yeah. I'm gonna call you back.

428
00:18:23.914 --> 00:18:26.349
The idea was a new technology.

429
00:18:26.383 --> 00:18:28.551
Nanobot facelifts
on an atomic level.

430
00:18:28.585 --> 00:18:30.553
No more laser nips and tucks.

431
00:18:30.587 --> 00:18:31.987
Microscopic robots programmed

432
00:18:32.022 --> 00:18:34.957
to rebuild the face
from the inside.

433
00:18:34.991 --> 00:18:37.593
Not a single scar.
At least not on the outside.

434
00:18:37.627 --> 00:18:39.428
- And?
- And...

435
00:18:39.463 --> 00:18:41.364
it did not go well.

436
00:18:41.398 --> 00:18:42.798
I wasn't involved in the trials.

437
00:18:42.833 --> 00:18:44.633
But I have to admit I was

438
00:18:44.668 --> 00:18:47.236
one of the first people
to really believe in it.

439
00:18:47.270 --> 00:18:48.371
We still don't know why.

440
00:18:48.405 --> 00:18:50.406
Why what?

441
00:18:50.440 --> 00:18:52.375
It was stopping people's hearts.

442
00:18:54.544 --> 00:18:56.979
On the victim. we found a mark
right at the...

443
00:18:57.013 --> 00:18:58.414
At the base of the skull.

444
00:18:58.448 --> 00:19:00.216
Yeah. the device
that inserts the nanobots

445
00:19:00.250 --> 00:19:02.551
into the neck
is called an actuator.

446
00:19:02.586 --> 00:19:03.853
Uh. let's say

447
00:19:03.887 --> 00:19:06.989
you wanted his perfect nose.

448
00:19:07.024 --> 00:19:08.491
The actuator injects
the nanobots

449
00:19:08.525 --> 00:19:10.192
into the target area.

450
00:19:10.227 --> 00:19:11.994
They're programmed to collect
his genetic blueprint.

451
00:19:12.029 --> 00:19:13.929
Then the actuator
would draw them out again.

452
00:19:13.964 --> 00:19:15.598
and then they'd be
injected into you.

453
00:19:15.632 --> 00:19:17.366
The patient.

454
00:19:17.401 --> 00:19:18.934
Rebuilding your nose
to look exactly like his.

455
00:19:18.969 --> 00:19:20.569
All done from the inside.

456
00:19:20.604 --> 00:19:22.171
The problem was

457
00:19:22.205 --> 00:19:23.839
the electricity caused
by the nanobots

458
00:19:23.874 --> 00:19:25.841
somehow triggered an arrhythmia
in the donor's heart

459
00:19:25.876 --> 00:19:27.243
until it stopped.

460
00:19:27.277 --> 00:19:29.512
The donors were dying.

461
00:19:31.882 --> 00:19:34.617
Some of the recipients
in the study

462
00:19:34.651 --> 00:19:37.353
were substantially disfigured.

463
00:19:43.160 --> 00:19:45.161
Where would someone
find an actuator

464
00:19:45.195 --> 00:19:47.630
to do this procedure?

465
00:19:52.335 --> 00:19:55.104
The nanobots followed
their blueprint perfectly.

466
00:19:55.138 --> 00:19:57.973
You're one step closer
to your ideal face.

467
00:19:59.676 --> 00:20:01.977
Let's keep going.

468
00:20:03.347 --> 00:20:05.981
Now.

469
00:20:06.016 --> 00:20:08.150
When will it ever
be enough. Eric?

470
00:20:12.356 --> 00:20:14.156
You know I know
all about the risks.

471
00:20:15.492 --> 00:20:17.126
You know I don't care.

472
00:20:17.160 --> 00:20:20.997
What you did to me
was worse than dying.

473
00:20:21.031 --> 00:20:23.632
You volunteered for the trials.

474
00:20:25.702 --> 00:20:27.169
Do it.

475
00:20:50.761 --> 00:20:53.062
I don't like what that stuff
does to me.

476
00:20:53.096 --> 00:20:56.465
You know I have to flood
your system with adrenaline.

477
00:20:56.500 --> 00:20:57.700
boost your physical strength.

478
00:20:57.734 --> 00:20:58.801
or you will never survive

479
00:20:58.835 --> 00:21:00.269
another procedure so soon.

480
00:21:04.207 --> 00:21:05.441
(gasps)

481
00:21:05.475 --> 00:21:06.776
(exhales)

482
00:21:07.944 --> 00:21:09.979
(beeps)

483
00:21:10.013 --> 00:21:11.714
(machinery whirring)

484
00:21:11.748 --> 00:21:13.482
(panting)

485
00:21:15.519 --> 00:21:18.020
(groaning)

486
00:21:19.222 --> 00:21:20.790
(groaning continues)

487
00:21:20.824 --> 00:21:22.725
(screaming)

488
00:21:25.595 --> 00:21:27.730
(screaming stops)

489
00:21:56.526 --> 00:21:58.661
They're beautiful.

490
00:22:03.200 --> 00:22:05.334
You know. it's okay
to have flaws. John.

491
00:22:05.369 --> 00:22:07.503
Whatever helps you sleep.

492
00:22:07.537 --> 00:22:09.739
It is said that
the more flaws you have.

493
00:22:09.773 --> 00:22:10.940
the more human you are.

494
00:22:10.974 --> 00:22:12.441
Have I told you how very human

495
00:22:12.476 --> 00:22:14.010
you are lately?

496
00:22:14.044 --> 00:22:15.778
You know. sometimes
when you're doing this.

497
00:22:15.812 --> 00:22:17.780
I'm not really listening.

498
00:22:19.149 --> 00:22:20.750
I don't have that many flaws.

499
00:22:20.784 --> 00:22:21.951
Your left eye
is one half millimeter

500
00:22:21.985 --> 00:22:23.419
higher than the right.

501
00:22:23.453 --> 00:22:25.388
Your nose has an abnormality
one inch from the base.

502
00:22:25.422 --> 00:22:27.323
Yeah. that's from being
punched in the face.

503
00:22:27.357 --> 00:22:28.791
Adds character.

504
00:22:28.825 --> 00:22:30.126
You have a fertile unibrow

505
00:22:30.160 --> 00:22:31.560
that you tend to regularly.

506
00:22:31.595 --> 00:22:33.262
At least it's my face.

507
00:22:33.297 --> 00:22:35.231
I know where I came from.

508
00:22:35.265 --> 00:22:37.366
You're a composite; who
knows where you came from?

509
00:22:37.401 --> 00:22:39.135
(phone rings)
Just think about that.

510
00:22:39.169 --> 00:22:40.536
Kennex.

511
00:22:40.570 --> 00:22:41.804
VALERIE:
Hey. John. where are you?

512
00:22:41.838 --> 00:22:43.939
I'm on my way to Chinatown.

513
00:22:43.974 --> 00:22:45.608
Near the Wall.

514
00:22:45.642 --> 00:22:46.909
We've got another victim.

515
00:22:46.943 --> 00:22:48.244
What have you got?

516
00:22:48.278 --> 00:22:50.413
I have an informant
who knows everything

517
00:22:50.447 --> 00:22:51.681
about the black market.

518
00:22:51.715 --> 00:22:52.915
We're trying to find
an actuator.

519
00:22:52.949 --> 00:22:54.216
What's an actuator?

520
00:22:54.251 --> 00:22:56.185
It's what our guy is using
to kill these people.

521
00:22:56.219 --> 00:22:57.586
I want to see
if I can track one.

522
00:22:57.621 --> 00:22:59.388
find out where he got it.

523
00:22:59.423 --> 00:23:01.624
The latest victim has
the same M.O.

524
00:23:01.658 --> 00:23:03.459
Heart stops. small wound

525
00:23:03.493 --> 00:23:05.695
at the back of the neck.

526
00:23:05.729 --> 00:23:07.997
John. the last seven murders
were each a month apart.

527
00:23:08.031 --> 00:23:10.766
and the last two victims
were within 48 hours.

528
00:23:10.801 --> 00:23:12.268
This guy's accelerating.

529
00:23:12.302 --> 00:23:15.237
We need to stop him.

530
00:23:16.673 --> 00:23:18.153
DORIAN:
You chew with your mouth open.

531
00:23:18.175 --> 00:23:20.276
you lie about putting gel
in your hair.

532
00:23:20.310 --> 00:23:21.277
and you snore.

533
00:23:21.311 --> 00:23:22.545
JOHN:
How do you know I snore?

534
00:23:22.579 --> 00:23:24.447
Your smartbed told me.

535
00:23:24.481 --> 00:23:26.983
Oh. I didn't realize you
two had a relationship.

536
00:23:27.017 --> 00:23:28.284
What else did it tell you?

537
00:23:28.318 --> 00:23:29.585
I don't know.

538
00:23:29.619 --> 00:23:31.988
Whatever it was.
I purged it from my data.

539
00:23:32.022 --> 00:23:33.422
Apparently.
I didn't want to remember.

540
00:23:33.457 --> 00:23:35.358
(sighs) Good.

541
00:23:35.392 --> 00:23:38.794
So what does this informant
look like?

542
00:23:38.829 --> 00:23:40.930
I'll know him when I see him.

543
00:23:40.964 --> 00:23:43.132
(crowd cheering)

544
00:23:51.008 --> 00:23:54.443
I hate to see robots used
for entertainment like this.

545
00:23:54.478 --> 00:23:56.612
(cheering continues)

546
00:24:07.190 --> 00:24:09.692
(cheering continues)

547
00:24:17.167 --> 00:24:20.803
You know a guy called Dicarlo?

548
00:24:21.705 --> 00:24:23.406
No.

549
00:24:28.378 --> 00:24:30.858
DORIAN:
What are you doing. man?

550
00:24:33.350 --> 00:24:35.384
Hey. Dicarlo.

551
00:24:36.753 --> 00:24:39.221
Damn it. Kennex!

552
00:24:40.557 --> 00:24:42.558
I thought you were dead.

553
00:24:42.592 --> 00:24:44.126
Glad to see me?

554
00:24:44.161 --> 00:24:46.896
Do you have any idea
how expensive these things are?

555
00:24:46.930 --> 00:24:48.097
Huh?!

556
00:24:48.131 --> 00:24:49.832
Dorian. Dicarlo.

557
00:24:49.866 --> 00:24:51.534
Dicarlo. Dorian.

558
00:24:57.427 --> 00:24:59.628
(crowd cheering)

559
00:24:59.653 --> 00:25:01.587
That was my favorite exosuit.

560
00:25:01.622 --> 00:25:03.923
Super comfy on the inside

561
00:25:03.957 --> 00:25:06.225
and sweet like pie
on the outside.

562
00:25:06.260 --> 00:25:08.094
Look. I need your help.

563
00:25:08.128 --> 00:25:10.797
I want to find something
called an actuator.

564
00:25:10.831 --> 00:25:11.964
That's what it looks like.

565
00:25:13.834 --> 00:25:15.535
Look at it.

566
00:25:15.569 --> 00:25:17.804
- I am looking.
- Look at it like you mean it.

567
00:25:17.838 --> 00:25:19.872
It's used in
illegal high-end

568
00:25:19.907 --> 00:25:21.107
plastic surgery.

569
00:25:21.141 --> 00:25:22.375
Plastic surgery?

570
00:25:22.409 --> 00:25:23.409
Yeah. the kind that kills

571
00:25:23.443 --> 00:25:24.744
the person whose face you want.

572
00:25:24.778 --> 00:25:26.913
You know where I can
find something like that?

573
00:25:26.947 --> 00:25:28.948
What do I get out of it?

574
00:25:28.982 --> 00:25:31.551
Look. you either help us out
of the goodness of your heart.

575
00:25:31.585 --> 00:25:34.020
or I'll get my robot to
toss you and your suit

576
00:25:34.054 --> 00:25:35.421
over the Wall.

577
00:25:37.658 --> 00:25:39.358
Okay. look.

578
00:25:39.393 --> 00:25:41.794
there's a guy.
and if there's heat on you.

579
00:25:41.829 --> 00:25:43.963
he can change your face
so facial rec

580
00:25:43.997 --> 00:25:45.465
won't recognize you.

581
00:25:45.499 --> 00:25:46.866
Is this guy a doctor?

582
00:25:46.900 --> 00:25:48.601
I don't know. Probably.

583
00:25:48.635 --> 00:25:49.735
Where do we find him?

584
00:25:49.770 --> 00:25:51.771
In the East Term.

585
00:25:55.943 --> 00:25:58.411
(sirens wailing)

586
00:25:59.880 --> 00:26:02.915
(computer chirping)

587
00:26:04.017 --> 00:26:07.153
(beeping)

588
00:26:08.222 --> 00:26:10.857
(knocking)

589
00:26:10.891 --> 00:26:12.792
JOHN:
Police. Open up.

590
00:26:15.429 --> 00:26:17.663
- Police. Open up.
- No. no. no.

591
00:26:25.873 --> 00:26:27.440
(bellowing)

592
00:26:27.474 --> 00:26:30.309
(grunting)

593
00:26:32.679 --> 00:26:34.347
A little help here?!

594
00:26:35.082 --> 00:26:36.949
(choking)

595
00:26:38.585 --> 00:26:41.888
(gasping)

596
00:26:41.922 --> 00:26:43.456
He's gone into cardiac arrest.

597
00:26:43.490 --> 00:26:45.391
(electrical whirring)

598
00:26:53.267 --> 00:26:54.634
(panting)

599
00:26:54.668 --> 00:26:56.502
DORIAN:
He's dead.

600
00:26:56.537 --> 00:27:00.006
Looks like he took a shot
of synthetic adrenaline.

601
00:27:00.040 --> 00:27:01.707
He was freakishly strong.

602
00:27:01.742 --> 00:27:04.444
Thought he was gonna
fight his way out.

603
00:27:04.478 --> 00:27:06.746
Whatever this guy was into.
he didn't want to get caught.

604
00:27:06.780 --> 00:27:08.514
You think?

605
00:27:10.083 --> 00:27:12.018
His name is Dr. Curtis McCann.

606
00:27:12.052 --> 00:27:13.686
Was.

607
00:27:13.720 --> 00:27:17.323
He was one of the 20 doctors
involved in the nanobot trials.

608
00:27:17.357 --> 00:27:18.658
He lost his medical license

609
00:27:18.692 --> 00:27:20.226
for hiding the side effects.

610
00:27:20.260 --> 00:27:21.861
(computer chirping)

611
00:27:21.895 --> 00:27:25.932
Dorian. here's the guy
we're looking for.

612
00:27:27.968 --> 00:27:29.235
This face is a composite

613
00:27:29.269 --> 00:27:30.703
of the specific features
of the victims.

614
00:27:30.737 --> 00:27:33.339
There are ten parts
to this facial construction.

615
00:27:33.373 --> 00:27:35.608
These are the
facial features he wants.

616
00:27:35.642 --> 00:27:37.110
There have only been
nine victims so far.

617
00:27:37.144 --> 00:27:39.512
Means there's still
one out there.

618
00:27:39.546 --> 00:27:42.749
Can you extrapolate
who the next victim's gonna be?

619
00:27:44.418 --> 00:27:47.286
According to facial rec.
this looks like the next victim.

620
00:27:47.321 --> 00:27:50.189
Looks like he selected
the cheekbone structure.

621
00:27:51.091 --> 00:27:53.426
Stahl. we think we know

622
00:27:53.460 --> 00:27:56.596
who the next victim's
going to be.

623
00:28:00.267 --> 00:28:02.101
Freeze!
This is the police.

624
00:28:02.136 --> 00:28:03.136
Sweep the perimeter.

625
00:28:03.137 --> 00:28:04.303
Jonathan Geddes?

626
00:28:04.338 --> 00:28:05.505
What the hell is this?

627
00:28:05.539 --> 00:28:06.939
(sighs)

628
00:28:06.974 --> 00:28:08.908
We're here to protect you.

629
00:28:11.478 --> 00:28:12.779
What have you got?

630
00:28:12.813 --> 00:28:13.880
Nothing yet.

631
00:28:13.914 --> 00:28:15.114
We've got a plainclothes
downstairs.

632
00:28:15.149 --> 00:28:16.916
<i>but we're ready for him up here</i>

633
00:28:16.950 --> 00:28:19.852
<i>if he makes it past him.</i>

634
00:28:19.887 --> 00:28:21.454
Any more info
on the killer's I.D.?

635
00:28:21.488 --> 00:28:23.623
We subpoenaed the insurance
company to get the names

636
00:28:23.657 --> 00:28:25.758
of the patients in the trials.

637
00:28:25.793 --> 00:28:28.027
Might take a few days
to get through the red tape.

638
00:28:28.061 --> 00:28:29.382
VALERIE:
<i>We don't have that long.</i>

639
00:28:29.396 --> 00:28:32.231
JOHN:
<i>Tell me about it.</i>

640
00:28:37.404 --> 00:28:39.038
(phone ringing)

641
00:28:39.072 --> 00:28:41.174
Hold on a minute.

642
00:28:43.043 --> 00:28:45.144
(ringing continues)

643
00:28:49.283 --> 00:28:50.550
Who is it?

644
00:28:50.584 --> 00:28:52.452
The call is scrambled.
Answer it.

645
00:28:52.486 --> 00:28:53.886
And say what?
I don't know.

646
00:28:53.921 --> 00:28:55.521
Just-just use his voice.
you know.

647
00:28:55.556 --> 00:28:56.789
like you... like you do mine.

648
00:28:56.824 --> 00:28:58.458
I have never heard his voice.

649
00:28:58.492 --> 00:29:00.653
I've only heard him grunt
when he was kicking your ass.

650
00:29:00.661 --> 00:29:02.361
(ringing continues)

651
00:29:06.900 --> 00:29:08.935
(ringing stops)
(sighs) Terrific.

652
00:29:08.969 --> 00:29:11.270
JOHN:
Hey. I'm back. Sorry.

653
00:29:11.305 --> 00:29:14.140
He's not gonna give up
when he's just one piece away.

654
00:29:14.174 --> 00:29:16.042
JOHN: <i> He's been selecting
his victims carefully.</i>

655
00:29:16.076 --> 00:29:18.277
<i>He'll find someone else</i>
<i>with the feature he needs.</i>

656
00:29:18.312 --> 00:29:20.580
<i>It's just a matter of time.</i>

657
00:29:25.552 --> 00:29:27.653
♪ Oh... ♪

658
00:29:29.890 --> 00:29:33.860
♪ Now. I don't hardly know her ♪

659
00:29:36.196 --> 00:29:40.633
♪ But I think I could love her ♪

660
00:29:42.970 --> 00:29:45.471
♪ Crimson and clover ♪

661
00:29:49.309 --> 00:29:51.677
♪ I... ♪

662
00:29:53.881 --> 00:29:57.750
♪ Wish she'd come walking over ♪

663
00:29:59.319 --> 00:30:04.257
♪ Now. I've been waiting
to show her ♪

664
00:30:06.527 --> 00:30:10.363
♪ Crimson and clover ♪

665
00:30:12.466 --> 00:30:16.402
♪ Over and over ♪

666
00:30:18.739 --> 00:30:21.340
♪ Over and over... ♪

667
00:30:25.268 --> 00:30:27.477
How is he choosing his
victims?

668
00:30:27.508 --> 00:30:29.214
He has the perfect
face in mind.

669
00:30:29.248 --> 00:30:31.383
and he's found the victims
with those features.

670
00:30:31.417 --> 00:30:33.885
VALERIE: They have one
other thing in common.

671
00:30:33.919 --> 00:30:36.399
They all live in
the Lower Term.

672
00:30:36.422 --> 00:30:40.058
Well. that narrows it down
to half a million... people.

673
00:30:42.795 --> 00:30:44.095
MALDONADO:
What is it?

674
00:30:46.132 --> 00:30:48.366
Take a look at my driver's
license. What do you see?

675
00:30:48.401 --> 00:30:50.602
A terrible picture.
You should have it redone.

676
00:30:50.636 --> 00:30:52.904
Yeah. I tried. but you have
to wait in line for hours

677
00:30:52.938 --> 00:30:56.574
to get the new 3-D pictures.
which all of these people have.

678
00:30:56.609 --> 00:30:59.310
Maybe where they lived
is the pattern after all.

679
00:30:59.345 --> 00:31:00.879
Overlay the DMV district.

680
00:31:00.913 --> 00:31:03.982
DORIAN: They all fall
in the same district.

681
00:31:04.016 --> 00:31:05.784
Do you think the guy
works at the DMV?

682
00:31:05.818 --> 00:31:07.485
VALERIE: That's the only
connection we have.

683
00:31:07.520 --> 00:31:08.787
Let's check it out.

684
00:31:09.822 --> 00:31:11.690
(computer beeps)

685
00:31:11.713 --> 00:31:14.103
__

686
00:31:23.258 --> 00:31:24.753
__

687
00:31:24.770 --> 00:31:26.538
♪ ♪

688
00:31:28.451 --> 00:31:31.268
__

689
00:31:33.708 --> 00:31:35.847
__

690
00:31:38.700 --> 00:31:41.854
__

691
00:31:41.887 --> 00:31:45.123
♪ ♪

692
00:31:46.523 --> 00:31:48.475
__

693
00:31:53.350 --> 00:31:56.654
__

694
00:31:56.673 --> 00:31:58.037
__

695
00:32:04.496 --> 00:32:09.583
__

696
00:32:09.615 --> 00:32:12.050
♪ ♪

697
00:32:14.757 --> 00:32:16.347
__

698
00:32:16.365 --> 00:32:17.554
__

699
00:32:22.561 --> 00:32:25.196
Guys.

700
00:32:25.231 --> 00:32:27.599
I got something.

701
00:32:27.633 --> 00:32:28.733
What'd you find?

702
00:32:28.768 --> 00:32:30.402
I think I found him.

703
00:32:30.436 --> 00:32:31.936
He did work at the DMV.

704
00:32:31.971 --> 00:32:33.505
His name is Eric Latham.

705
00:32:33.539 --> 00:32:35.206
JOHN:
Can we be sure it's him?

706
00:32:35.241 --> 00:32:36.207
He went on disability

707
00:32:36.242 --> 00:32:38.076
September 9. a year ago.

708
00:32:38.110 --> 00:32:39.644
That's when the trials
were beginning.

709
00:32:39.678 --> 00:32:42.180
Do you think he still
has access to the DMV files?

710
00:32:42.214 --> 00:32:44.683
He could. Technically.
he's still an employee.

711
00:32:44.717 --> 00:32:47.652
He's had 32 surgeries
in the last seven years.

712
00:32:47.687 --> 00:32:50.355
MALDONADO: Why would he
volunteer for these trials?

713
00:32:50.389 --> 00:32:52.691
He looks perfectly normal.

714
00:32:52.725 --> 00:32:54.192
And there's nothing
in his medical history

715
00:32:54.226 --> 00:32:55.560
that shows he was
disfigured. either.

716
00:32:55.594 --> 00:32:58.063
<i>Could be dysmorphic disorder.</i>

717
00:32:58.097 --> 00:33:00.398
<i>He sees images of perfection</i>
<i>all around him.</i>

718
00:33:00.433 --> 00:33:02.834
<i>and the more he compares</i>
<i>himself to those images.</i>

719
00:33:02.868 --> 00:33:04.803
<i>the worse he feels</i>
<i>about himself.</i>

720
00:33:04.837 --> 00:33:06.304
<i>and he's compelled</i>
<i>to take the steps</i>

721
00:33:06.339 --> 00:33:07.439
to mitigate the disaster

722
00:33:07.473 --> 00:33:08.973
he sees in the mirror.

723
00:33:09.008 --> 00:33:10.542
That's not a disaster.

724
00:33:10.576 --> 00:33:12.177
VALERIE:
<i>To him. it is.</i>

725
00:33:12.211 --> 00:33:14.211
<i>He wants to be</i>
<i>his version of perfect.</i>

726
00:33:19.352 --> 00:33:21.052
Go get him.

727
00:33:21.087 --> 00:33:22.454
Good job.

728
00:33:37.169 --> 00:33:39.104
OFFICER:
Bedroom's clear!

729
00:33:39.138 --> 00:33:40.305
Bathroom's clear.

730
00:33:41.640 --> 00:33:42.741
Clear!

731
00:33:44.443 --> 00:33:46.644
He's gone.

732
00:33:46.679 --> 00:33:48.146
OFFICER: Code four...
area is secure.

733
00:33:50.016 --> 00:33:51.650
His terminal's encrypted.

734
00:33:53.416 --> 00:33:55.896
JOHN:
What do you got?

735
00:33:55.921 --> 00:33:57.401
DORIAN: He's using a
composite picture

736
00:33:57.423 --> 00:33:59.591
of his ideal face
as his avatar.

737
00:33:59.625 --> 00:34:01.993
His only correspondence
was with one woman.

738
00:34:02.028 --> 00:34:03.595
Online.
They chatted every day.

739
00:34:03.629 --> 00:34:05.130
JOHN:
Who is she?

740
00:34:05.164 --> 00:34:06.464
DORIAN:
Her screen name is Judy.

741
00:34:06.499 --> 00:34:07.866
They communicated this morning.

742
00:34:07.900 --> 00:34:09.801
They've been corresponding
for months.

743
00:34:09.835 --> 00:34:11.936
He told her he lives in Arizona.

744
00:34:11.971 --> 00:34:13.138
They've never met.

745
00:34:13.172 --> 00:34:15.507
but he's using his real name.

746
00:34:15.541 --> 00:34:17.175
I don't think she's a victim.

747
00:34:17.209 --> 00:34:19.144
He's perfecting
his face for her.

748
00:34:19.178 --> 00:34:20.612
JOHN: Have you got her address?

749
00:34:20.646 --> 00:34:23.048
All I have is a screen name.

750
00:34:23.082 --> 00:34:25.383
With a little time.
I think I can track her

751
00:34:25.418 --> 00:34:27.898
through her IP address.

752
00:34:30.423 --> 00:34:31.856
She a brunette?

753
00:34:31.891 --> 00:34:33.124
Yes.

754
00:34:33.159 --> 00:34:35.360
Yes. she is.

755
00:34:35.394 --> 00:34:37.295
I think I found her.

756
00:34:38.597 --> 00:34:40.532
The food cartridges
are in the third bag.

757
00:34:40.566 --> 00:34:42.133
Do you need any help. Judy?

758
00:34:42.168 --> 00:34:43.902
No. I'm fine.
Thank you. Phil.

759
00:34:43.936 --> 00:34:45.270
Okay.

760
00:34:45.304 --> 00:34:47.172
See you next time.

761
00:34:54.013 --> 00:34:56.081
(door closes) ERIC: Judy...

762
00:34:56.115 --> 00:34:57.549
Judy. it's Eric.

763
00:34:58.751 --> 00:35:00.285
Eric?

764
00:35:00.319 --> 00:35:02.654
I didn't mean to scare you.

765
00:35:02.688 --> 00:35:06.725
Your. uh...
your door was open.

766
00:35:08.227 --> 00:35:10.061
I meant it as a surprise.

767
00:35:10.096 --> 00:35:11.896
Coming early. I mean.

768
00:35:14.600 --> 00:35:17.068
You're beautiful.

769
00:35:17.937 --> 00:35:20.071
Oh...

770
00:35:22.808 --> 00:35:24.943
I'm sorry about the bandage.

771
00:35:24.977 --> 00:35:26.644
Truth is.

772
00:35:26.679 --> 00:35:30.215
I didn't want you
to see me like this.

773
00:35:30.249 --> 00:35:32.217
But I can assure you

774
00:35:32.251 --> 00:35:34.786
I won't be wearing it for long.

775
00:35:36.155 --> 00:35:38.623
I'm sure you're beautiful.

776
00:35:38.658 --> 00:35:41.459
As beautiful as the feelings

777
00:35:41.494 --> 00:35:44.062
and the conversations
we've shared.

778
00:35:44.096 --> 00:35:47.732
But I've kept
something from you.

779
00:35:49.969 --> 00:35:51.436
What?

780
00:36:08.788 --> 00:36:10.455
You're blind.

781
00:36:10.489 --> 00:36:12.590
(sighs)

782
00:36:14.660 --> 00:36:16.895
I should have told you.

783
00:36:16.929 --> 00:36:18.430
I-I struggled with it
every time.

784
00:36:18.464 --> 00:36:20.565
but I just...

785
00:36:22.268 --> 00:36:23.902
I-I just liked you so much.

786
00:36:23.936 --> 00:36:26.171
and-and you liked me.
and I didn't want it to end.

787
00:36:26.205 --> 00:36:28.340
and I was afraid it would.

788
00:36:30.910 --> 00:36:34.279
If you could love me...

789
00:36:34.313 --> 00:36:36.614
then you would see
that I am the same person

790
00:36:36.649 --> 00:36:38.950
that you began to know
and care about.

791
00:36:40.219 --> 00:36:41.620
I just felt

792
00:36:41.654 --> 00:36:43.421
that you were...

793
00:36:43.456 --> 00:36:45.590
as lonely as I was.

794
00:36:48.094 --> 00:36:49.928
Was I wrong?

795
00:36:54.600 --> 00:36:56.701
No.

796
00:37:05.544 --> 00:37:07.312
I don't care about your face.

797
00:37:07.346 --> 00:37:09.347
or-or what you look like.
I just...

798
00:37:10.850 --> 00:37:13.718
I'm so happy
that we found each other.

799
00:37:33.639 --> 00:37:35.507
You're crying.

800
00:37:42.281 --> 00:37:44.015
(door opens)

801
00:37:44.050 --> 00:37:46.418
Eric! Eric!
Police! Police! Freeze!

802
00:37:46.452 --> 00:37:48.420
Police!
Ms. Wood. stay where you are.

803
00:37:48.454 --> 00:37:50.422
Suspect on premises.

804
00:38:01.470 --> 00:38:04.338
♪ ♪

805
00:38:10.379 --> 00:38:12.346
It's over. Eric.

806
00:38:20.222 --> 00:38:21.656
Come down from there. Eric.

807
00:38:23.859 --> 00:38:27.128
Look. I understand
how you must be feeling.

808
00:38:27.162 --> 00:38:30.031
It doesn't have
to end like this.

809
00:38:32.601 --> 00:38:34.035
What's your name?

810
00:38:34.069 --> 00:38:36.471
It's John.

811
00:38:38.273 --> 00:38:41.075
Have you ever been loved. John?

812
00:38:43.745 --> 00:38:45.646
I have.

813
00:38:45.681 --> 00:38:47.815
Then you wouldn't understand.

814
00:38:52.788 --> 00:38:55.723
We're supposed to be loved.

815
00:39:25.020 --> 00:39:27.922
♪ ♪

816
00:39:40.169 --> 00:39:41.409
You okay?

817
00:39:41.436 --> 00:39:43.571
Yeah. Yeah. I'm good.

818
00:39:45.171 --> 00:39:47.651
Do you think. with all
the people in this city...

819
00:39:47.676 --> 00:39:49.110
in the world...

820
00:39:49.144 --> 00:39:51.624
that there's someone
out there for everyone?

821
00:39:52.581 --> 00:39:54.048
I do.

822
00:39:55.887 --> 00:39:56.927
That's old-fashioned.

823
00:39:56.952 --> 00:39:57.919
That's me.

824
00:39:57.953 --> 00:39:58.920
(chuckles)

825
00:39:58.954 --> 00:40:01.222
Old-fashioned.

826
00:40:01.256 --> 00:40:04.158
Even my robot's discontinued.

827
00:40:04.193 --> 00:40:05.827
Do you want me to come
to a bar with you

828
00:40:05.861 --> 00:40:07.195
and watch you drink?

829
00:40:07.229 --> 00:40:09.330
(chuckles) No.

830
00:40:09.364 --> 00:40:10.565
No. that's okay.

831
00:40:10.599 --> 00:40:12.400
That. uh... got a little
weird last time.

832
00:40:12.434 --> 00:40:13.835
(chuckles)

833
00:40:14.870 --> 00:40:17.004
Good night. John.

834
00:40:30.889 --> 00:40:32.129
Hey. John.

835
00:40:32.154 --> 00:40:33.387
Hey.

836
00:40:33.422 --> 00:40:34.489
You going home?

837
00:40:34.523 --> 00:40:36.290
Yeah. I was thinking about it.

838
00:40:36.325 --> 00:40:38.993
I might head out for a drink.
You ever heard of

839
00:40:39.027 --> 00:40:41.329
a place called Leo's? That's
actually where I'm going right now.

840
00:40:41.363 --> 00:40:42.563
I love that place.

841
00:40:42.598 --> 00:40:43.959
Come on.
You're kidding me. Really?

842
00:40:43.966 --> 00:40:46.467
- Yeah.
- Detective Stahl.

843
00:40:46.502 --> 00:40:47.602
VALERIE:
Hi.

844
00:40:47.636 --> 00:40:48.636
I'm sorry. I'm...

845
00:40:48.670 --> 00:40:49.670
not interrupting. am I?

846
00:40:49.705 --> 00:40:51.739
No. No. not at all.

847
00:40:51.773 --> 00:40:53.207
Jake. this is John.

848
00:40:53.242 --> 00:40:54.876
Hey. How are you?

849
00:40:54.910 --> 00:40:56.444
- You ready?
- Yeah.

850
00:40:56.478 --> 00:40:57.845
Will I see you there?

851
00:40:57.880 --> 00:40:59.747
Yeah. Yeah. I might swing along.

852
00:40:59.781 --> 00:41:00.982
You know. but...

853
00:41:01.016 --> 00:41:03.217
got a few reports
to finish. but...

854
00:41:03.252 --> 00:41:04.852
You guys have fun.

855
00:41:04.887 --> 00:41:06.954
Don't work too hard.

856
00:41:29.178 --> 00:41:31.279
♪ Worlds away ♪

857
00:41:31.313 --> 00:41:34.615
♪ With memories ♪

858
00:41:34.650 --> 00:41:38.085
♪ Of killing time and dreams ♪

859
00:41:39.354 --> 00:41:41.322
♪ Think of me ♪

860
00:41:41.356 --> 00:41:44.125
♪ It was so cold ♪

861
00:41:44.159 --> 00:41:46.394
♪ We burned ♪

862
00:41:49.164 --> 00:41:51.799
♪ And as they leave ♪

863
00:41:51.834 --> 00:41:54.202
♪ They cross my mind ♪

864
00:41:54.236 --> 00:41:55.937
♪ No time ♪

865
00:41:55.971 --> 00:41:58.773
♪ I think it's over ♪

866
00:41:58.807 --> 00:42:03.077
♪ This life inside
I seem to mind ♪

867
00:42:03.111 --> 00:42:08.568
♪ Look in your eyes.
you're worlds away... ♪

868
00:42:08.584 --> 00:42:10.486
